<br>
The nice thing about fixed point systems is that it is very hard for them to be abused.  Nothing will tear a guild up quicker than RPP/DKP/whatever abuse.  The problem with them is that you have stuff rotting, wasting time for your guild.<br>
<br>
I'm a fan of tier pricing with decreasing values.  <br>
I'm not going to write the whole system up, I'm sure there are a million published variations. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=reyek>Reyek</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=90184" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Minstrel</span><br>  Posts: 34<br> <font color=#330000>(6/4/04 10:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19464.topic&index=5>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sigh, ELP vs DKP?</span><hr size=1> We use a bidding system which accounts for the flux in desirability over time as a zone is farmed which I like, if you want an item bad enough you'll bid accordingly or wait a few weeks/months and get it cheaper. It also prevents alot of stuff from rotting like class specific items which seems logical to me. Letting things rot due to pricing or not being able to afford is detrimental to a guild and seems to me would slow down growth substantially. It sounds like whomever is doing the pricing for your guild doesn't understand bards at all. I would agree with Bay, looks like that system needs an overhaul. <p><div align="center"><embed width="450" height="150" <img border=0 src="http://home.comcast.net/~tydevoe/birdsig.swf"/></div></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=quelinqrystalsinger>Quelin Qrystalsinger</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.smart-code.net/pictures/sigs/keys.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> Posts: 890<br> <font color=#330000>(6/4/04 10:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19464.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.smart-code.net/pictures/sigs/smallav.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sigh, ELP vs DKP?</span><hr size=1> I agree, letting stuff rot is silly and wasteful, espically useful items like the TZ neck even if a bard didn't want it the focus effect and stats would be nice for healers.   <br>
<br>
Anyway, we use a merit council which I believe is mostly officers on at the time and a few classes there are not officers for also give imput.  We keep track of attendance and your overall loot (Its public on the internal board) and most of our meriting of loot is based upon that.   Items have values based upon their HP / Mana score and if nobody wants an item you can pick it up for a minor amount of points instead of letting it rot.  If nobody wishes to do so or stick it on a bot then it rots.<br>
<br>
We had some items with people not picking up valid upgrades and them going to more rot status before we gave items values.  I mean who wants to get a Time 1 item when its counted the same as a BP, T5 or Quarm loot?  Yes thought not.  So they did the hp/mana valuaing and nothing being a free loot to cut down on that.  <br>
<br>
We also give attendance if your on and not able to join for flagging reasons because it encourages attendance not being able to join raids sucks and some newer members have some flagging issues.  Although I know some guilds dont do that (If you can't zone in to where we are raiding too bad no attendance for you) as well as if you get to sit in the ZI waiting for a Raid spot to open.  But we also have a pretty good list of who is flagged for what.<br>
<br>
<br>
I suppose its kind of close to DKP, but there is no cap if we get more loot in well that is fine, everyone's loot to attendance ratios will just be a little higher.   Also, we dont have to deal with direct bidding against guildmates and keeping track of points.  You never run out of any points so you dont have to worry about it.  However, some people like DKP (a good DKP anyway) because you can control the loot you get more directly and get what you want when it comes around.  Merit systems even our highly merit and previous loot based one tends to give loot based on guild priorities.<br>
<br>
 <br>
Every loot system is different, you just have to get something that works for your guild.   If your current system works and you just have a vocal minority asking for change make a thread going over all the pros and cons of the systems your looking at.   If whatever other system they are looking at is just a general idea make them hammer some points down then discuss it.   <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub26.ezboard.com/borderofthescatteredwinds">~OSW~</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=141580"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.smart-code.net/pictures/sigs/Que_sig4.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://24.26.194.253/">Avatar by Lyss</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ralkora>ralkora</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Minstrel</span><br>  Posts: 125<br> <font color=#330000>(6/4/04 11:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19464.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://209.61.189.164/forums/images/avatars/10/darkside1.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sigh, ELP vs DKP?</span><hr size=1> Very nice DKP system in my guild.  Points come in pretty slowly, but it's balanced out somewhat at the end of the month based on how much loot went to players.  (If shit rots, we don't earn as much heh.)<br>
